'''Gnome Air''' is a [[Gnomes|gnomish]] airline that is the primary overseer and manager of air travel in [[Gielinor]].{{CiteNPC|npc=Captain Errdo|loc=The Grand Tree|quote=Gnome Air is the finest airline in Gielinor! Well, it's the only real airline in Gielinor. Ha!}} It uses [[gnome gliders]], first invented by [[Oaknock the Engineer]] and his son [[Yewnock]] at the beginning of the [[Fifth Age]].{{CiteNPC|npc=Varrock Museum{{!}}Display case 10|loc=Varrock Museum|quote=They did mention that an old gnome engineer called Oaknock used to make model gliders for his children. Oaknock's son, Yewnock, ended up creating this method of transport with inspiration from his father's models.}} Until the arrest of the misanthropic [[Glough]], Gnome Air would only take gnomes, but now they also fly humans.

Whilst Gnome Air dominates long-distance air travel across the globe, [[Ali Morrisane]]’s fleet of [[magic carpet]]s is the main mode of transportation over shorter distances in the desert.{{CiteNPC|npc=Rug Merchant|loc=Kharidian Desert|quote=I don't think Ali is prepared to take on Gnome Air just yet. Their gliders are much faster than our carpets. Besides that, I think we are in the short-haul business, something that would only work in harsh conditions like the desert.}} When Ali announced his new venture, a PR executive for Gnome Air replied that 'it [would] never take off.'{{CiteNews|newsdate=5 July 2005|url=https://secure.runescape.com/m=news/magic-carpet-ride|title=Magic Carpet Ride}} In fact, the gnomes have filed lawsuits against Ali to the [[Supreme Rune Court]], the result of which is not known.{{CiteNews|newsdate=15 August 2005|url= http://services.runescape.com/m=news/rogue-trader|title=Rogue Trader}}

All the current gnome glider pilots are employed by Gnome Air, except [[Ninto]] and [[Daerkin]], who are retired, having tested Yewnock’s original prototypes.

